cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper applies basic data-mining methods to extract features and classify players based on their playing style and strength. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes applications for aiding in Go study and tuning of Go-playing programs, which falls under the scope of AI. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper discusses the extraction of summary information from a large corpus of game records, which can be seen as an information retrieval task. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper may involve natural language processing techniques to preprocess the game records and extract summary information. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper may have implications for the Go community and the way players are ranked and perceived, which falls under the scope of computers and society.
